OL,6,FHe says his children's time at school
OL,7,Fwas spent indoors and characterised by
OL,8,Fgetting into trouble; now, their days
OL,9,Fare spent learning outside and
OL,10,Fexploring their own hobbies and
OL,11,Finterests.
OL,13,F"They really thrive being outdoors
OL,14,Fwith their learning", he adds, "so we
OL,15,Ftry and keep any inside stuff to a
OL,16,Fminimum and integrate that with being
OL,17,Foutside most days".
