OL,6,FThey must provide educational plans
OL,7,Fand make sure their children are
OL,8,Fmeeting progress targets in line with
OL,9,Ftheir age and ability.
OL,11,FThey are also able to access
OL,12,Fgovernment resources such as training
OL,13,Fand development courses, Q&A sessions
OL,14,Fwith senior education officers,
OL,15,Fsupport from educational
OL,16,Fpsychologists, and funding for up to
OL,17,Ffive GCSE subjects.
